{"title":"Trek’s Latest Project One ICON Color Scheme is Speed Rendered in Paint","link":"https://bikerumor.com/trek-project-one-icon-disrupt/","date":1685372400000,"content":"<p>Trek’s <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/project-one-icon/\" target=\"_blank\">Project One ICON</a> initiative is all about <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-project-one-gets-groovy-with-hand-painted-tie-dye-finishes/\">high-end paint jobs</a> that capture the spirit of the bikes they adorn. The latest offering is called “Disrupt,” and it’s only available on what Trek calls “our fastest road bike” — <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/road-bikes/performance-road-bikes/madone/madone-slr/c/B213-1/\" target=\"_blank\">the Madone SLR</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Disrupt is a streaky smear of red, blue, and black stripes meant to invoke “the chaotic blur of the peloton racing by,” according to a Trek press release. It’s certainly eye-catching. And while the photos are nice, it probably really comes into its own once in motion. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-800x533.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-2048x1366.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-7-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-6.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-6-800x450.jpg\" alt s