5/trek-4-1536x1029.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-4-2048x1372.jpg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-800x450.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-3-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2.jpg\"><img width=\"800\" height=\"450\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-800x450.jpg\" alt srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-800x450.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-297x167.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-120x67.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-768x432.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-1536x864.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-2048x1152.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-400x225.jpg 400w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/trek-2-1200x675.jpg 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tip of the Madone SLR spear is the <a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/bikes/road-bikes/performance-road-bikes/madone/madone-slr/madone-slr-9-axs-gen-7/p/37420/?colorCode=blue\" target=\"_blank\">SLR 9 AXS Gen 7</a>. This puppy runs $13,200 MSRP and represents all the aero tech Trek could cram into one bicycle. The 800 Series OCLV Carbon frame paired with high-end components makes for a bike that is, Trek said on its website, “the ride you reach for on race day when every watt counts and your eyes are on the top step.” </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Madone SLRs in Disrupt are available now at Trek retailers and online at the Trek website. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.trekbikes.com/us/en_US/project-one-icon/\" target=\"_blank\">trek.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/trek-project-one-icon-disrupt/\">Trek’s Latest Project One ICON Color Scheme is Speed Rendered in Paint</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Andrew Marshall","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"2fcd3cec51f5115538401a105455adfc90fb53f41d995442c0966eb4dd5275b0","category":"Cycling"}